post_text:
Hickman Elementary qualified to be named a California Distinguished School. The application required us to identify a signature program. Although there are several things that HES does well, we chose to highlight the wonderful work that teachers have done to improve Mathematics achievement over the past several years. Our committed staff have spent hours attending trainings and implementing what they have learned in the classroom. The result is that our students significantly outperform the state and county averages. Recognizing the good work of HES, the state committee awarded Hickman Elementary with a California Distinguished School Award. Ms. Barnett and a small group of staff will be traveling to Southern California this weekend to accept the award on Monday.

Please share this with your friends and family and help us spread great news.

post_text:
ATTENTION HICKMAN FAMILIES

Due to safety concerns surrounding increased flow rates of the Tuolumne River, the Hickman Road Bridge (Waterford-Hickman) will be closed on Monday afternoon or early evening. It is unclear at this point how long the bridge will be closed.

Until further notice, parents should plan on using alternative routes to transport their students to school. In addition, OUR SCHOOL BUS RUN TO WATERFORD WILL BE CANCELLED for the time being. A map has been included below and the following bridges over the Tuolumne River will remain open:

• Roberts Ferry Bridge
• Geer Road Bridge
• Santa Fe Bridge

Please give yourself enough time to get to your destination and drive safely.

post_text:
Harvest Carnival and Turkey Dinner

When: October 29 from 4PM to 8PM
Where: Hickman School

The Annual Harvest Carnival and Sixth Grade Turkey Dinner Fundraiser is a fun-filled community event. The proceeds from the Harvest Carnival benefit all the district's students by providing funds for enrichment and extracurricular activities. The Turkey Dinner helps send 6th graders to Camp Sea Lab.

Carnival tickets are 25 cents a ticket. Tickets may be purchased in $1.00 or $5.00 bundles at the carnival.

Turkey dinner tickets can be purchased in advance for $10.00 each. The dinner is from 4:30-7:30 and includes: turkey, stuffing, mashed potatoes & gravy, green beans, salad, dessert, and drinks.

If you would like more information regarding the Harvest Carnival, please call HIckman Schools at 209-874-1816 or 209-556-6540.

post_text: The district is in need of the a school nurse to work with all three of our schools 2 days per week. While a certificated school nurse would be preferred, we are taking applications from RN's with a 4 year degree as well. Applicants without a school nursing certificate would need to agree to pursue that under an emergency credential. Please share this with those that might be interested. For more information and to apply online, go to https://www.edjoin.org/Home/JobPosting/717534
